            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EWith%20these%20words%2C%20Jesus%20addressed%20His%20brothers%20who%20were%20pressuring%20Him%20to%20go%20to%20Jerusalem%20and%20perform%20miracles.%20They%20reasoned%20that%20anyone%20who%20wanted%20to%20be%20a%20public%20figure%20needed%20to%20go%20to%20the%20center%20of%20attention%20and%20promote%20himself.%20In%20their%20minds%2C%20Jesus%20had%20the%20greatest%20miracle%20show%20going%20and%20needed%20to%20advertise%20it!%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EJesus%20countered%20His%20brothers'%20demands%20with%20a%20reference%20to%20His%20time.%20He%20was%20committed%20to%20waiting%20upon%20the%20Lord%20for%20the%20right%20time%20with%20regard%20to%20doors%20of%20ministry.%20Many%20Christians%2C%20however%2C%20are%20more%20like%20Jesus'%20brothers%20than%20like%20Him.%20%20They%20look%20at%20ministry%20like%20it's%20a%20business%2C%20and%20they%20grow%20frustrated%20if%20they%20or%20anyone%20else%20misses%20an%20opportunity.%20%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESaul%2C%20too%2C%20had%20no%20sense%20of%20divine%20timing%20(1%20Samuel%2013%3A11-12).%20Instead%20of%20waiting%20for%20Samuel%20to%20make%20the%20sacrifice%2C%20he%20forced%20himself%20to%20offer%20it%20before%20the%20people%20began%20to%20scatter.%20This%20mistake%20of%20timing%20cost%20him%20his%20throne.%20%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20great%20eagle%20digs%20his%20claws%20into%20the%20top%20of%20the%20rock%20and%20waits%20for%20the%20thermal%20winds.%20When%20they%20are%20blowing%20too%20hard%20to%20resist%2C%20he%20releases%20his%20talons%20and%20soars.%20His%20wings%20do%20not%20flap%20with%20exertion%2C%20but%20he%20effortlessly%20soars%20high.%20Wait%20for%20the%20Lord%20and%20His%20winds%20of%20opportunity.%20He%20will%20exalt%20you%20when%20the%20timing%20is%20perfect.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
